\p
\v 11 And the priest shall offer the one for a sin offering, and the other for a burnt offering, and make an atonement for him, for that he sinned through the dead, and shall hallow his head that same day.
\p
\v 12 And he shall consecrate unto the LORD the days of his separation, and shall bring a lamb of the first year for a trespass offering: but the days that were before shall be lost, because his separation was defiled.
\p
\v 13 ¶ And this \add is\add* the law of the Nazarite, when the days of his separation are fulfilled: he shall be brought unto the door of the tabernacle of the congregation:
\p
\v 14 And he shall offer his offering unto the LORD, one he lamb of the first year without blemish for a burnt offering, and one ewe lamb of the first year without blemish for a sin offering, and one ram without blemish for peace offerings,
\p
\v 15 And a basket of unleavened bread, cakes of fine flour mingled with oil, and wafers of unleavened bread anointed with oil, and their meal offering, and their drink offerings.
\p
\v 16 And the priest shall bring \add them\add* before the LORD, and shall offer his sin offering, and his burnt offering:
\p
\v 17 And he shall offer the ram \add for\add* a sacrifice of peace offerings unto the LORD, with the basket of unleavened bread: the priest shall offer also his meal offering, and his drink offering.
\p
\v 18 And the Nazarite shall shave the head of his separation \add at\add* the door of the tabernacle of the congregation, and shall take the hair of the head of his separation, and put \add it\add* in the fire which \add is\add* under the sacrifice of the peace offerings.
\p
\v 19 And the priest shall take the boiled shoulder of the ram, and one unleavened cake out of the basket, and one unleavened wafer, and shall put \add them\add* upon the hands of the Nazarite, after \add the hair of\add* his separation is shaven:
\p
\v 20 And the priest shall wave them \add for\add* a wave offering before the LORD: this \add is\add* holy for the priest, with the wave breast and heave shoulder: and after that the Nazarite may drink wine.
\p
\v 21 This \add is\add* the law of the Nazarite who hath vowed, \add and of\add* his offering unto the LORD for his separation, beside that \add that\add* his hand shall get: according to the vow which he vowed, so he must do after the law of his separation.
\p
\v 22 ¶ And the LORD spake unto Moses, saying,
\p
\v 23 Speak unto Aaron and unto his sons, saying, On this wise ye shall bless the children of Israel, saying unto them,
\p
\v 24 The LORD bless thee, and keep thee:
